<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 05 at 7:37AM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Patchy dense fog for the morning drive...
Motorists will likely encounter rapidly changing visibilities
this morning, possibly as low as one quarter mile or less. The
fog has formed along and north of US Highway 30 with the lowest
visibilities along and north of US Highway 6. If you encounter
dense fog, slow down, make sure to use low beam headlights and use
caution at intersections.
The fog will gradually decrease and visibility will improve after
9:00 AM EDT/8:00 AM CDT.</description>
